1. Go to an issue filter that only YOU can see, that displays the query in Advanced rather than basic mode.
2. Change part of the query - so in my case I do this a lot to copy a standard of filters from one project to another ... so I would edit the project="X" to a new value instead of X.
3. DO NOT SAVE, but instead, click "Details" to change the filter from private to Everyone/shared. Accept this.
4. A message saying the filter is SAVED comes up.
5. Go to another filter and back to this one. You'll see the sharing was saved, but the query has not been saved.

Ideas:
* Because you actually need to navigate away from the page, it would be a feature to try and save this between pages,
* Either that or change the success message from:
{quote}
Changes to <Filter Name> have been saved.
{quote}
to something more accurate (and true):
{quote}
Changes to the permissions of <Filter Name> have been saved.
{quote}

