h3. Steps to reproduce

#  Login to JIRA with an Administrator account;
#  Enable the text gadget as per [this documentation|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Adding+the+Text+Gadget];
# Browse to the system dashboard configuration (Administration -> System -> System Dashboard);
# Add a text gadget with any content;
# If you log out and browse to the system dashboard, the gadget is not visible, as if it had some kind of permission which could be preventing the content from being seen by any user;

h3. Why is this a bug?

This gadget has no permission level to be set. If you take the example of a gadget filter, this includes permissions from the filter, etc. But the text gadget is only plain text and there is no permission involving its content, and so it should be visible by any user.

